    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1845-07-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1845-07-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="35"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d35">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 28.</note>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract. ]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Buchanan</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Pakenham</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1845-07-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 12, 1845.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>* * * He (the President) has, therefore, instructed the under signed again to
                    propose to the government of Great Britain that the Oregon Territory shall be
                    divided between the two countries by the forty-ninth parallel of north latitude,
                    from the Rocky Mountains to the Pacific Ocean; offering at the same time to make
                    *free to Great Britain, any port or ports on Vancouver’s Island, south of this
                    parallel, which the British government may desire. * * * * * * *<seg
                        type="margin">Mr. Buchanan offers the line of 49° with free ports on
                        Vancouver.</seg>
                    <seg type="margin">[32]</seg>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JAMES BUCHANAN.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Rt. Hon. R. <hi rend="smallcaps">Pakenham</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c.</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
